   "source": [
    "# $C_3$ and $C_6$ Coefficients"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The PairInteraction Python API comes with high-level functionality to calculate $C_3$ coefficients (dipole-dipole) and $C_6$ coefficients (van der Waals) without having to write much code. All functionality for calculating the coefficients are provided by the `pi.C3` and `pi.C6` classes:\n",
    "* The constructor of the classes take the state of interest.\n",
    "* The `get` method returns the coefficient.\n",
    "* The classes determine automatically which states should be taken into account to obtain an accurate coefficient. To provide guidance how many states in the pair basis should be considered, you can use the method `set_minimum_number_of_ket_pairs`.\n",
    "* If the coefficient should be calculated in the presence of e.g. a magnetic field, the `set_magnetic_field` method can be called before getting the coefficient. In general, the classes support similar setters as the `pi.SystemAtom` and `pi.SystemPair` classes.\n",
    "\n",
    "If you are interested in calculating effective Hamiltonians beyond just the $C_3$ and $C_6$ coefficients, also check out the tutorial [Effective Hamiltonians](./effective_hamiltonian.ipynb)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%pip install -q matplotlib numpy pairinteraction\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pairinteraction as pi\n",
    "\n",
    "if pi.Database.get_global_database() is None:\n",
    "    pi.Database.initialize_global_database(download_missing=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Quickly get a $C_3$ and $C_6$ coefficient"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In the following, we have a minimal example for calculating a $C_3$ and $C_6$ coefficient."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "C3 coefficient between |Rb:61,S_1/2,1/2⟩ and |Rb:62,P_3/2,1/2⟩: -99.956 MHz um^3\n",
      "C6 coefficient of (KetAtom(Rb:61,S_1/2,1/2), KetAtom(Rb:61,S_1/2,1/2)): 169208.742 MHz um^6\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ket1 = pi.KetAtom(\"Rb\", n=61, l=0, j=0.5, m=0.5)\n",
    "ket2 = pi.KetAtom(\"Rb\", n=62, l=1, j=1.5, m=0.5)\n",
    "\n",
    "c3 = pi.C3(ket1, ket2).get(\"MHz um^3\")\n",
    "print(f\"C3 coefficient between {ket1} and {ket2}: {c3:.3f} MHz um^3\")\n",
    "\n",
    "c6 = pi.C6(ket1, ket1).get(\"MHz um^6\")\n",
    "print(f\"C6 coefficient of {ket1, ket1}: {c6:.3f} MHz um^6\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Angular dependence of the $C_3$ and $C_6$ coefficient"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As a more sophisticated example, we calculate the angular dependence of the coefficients in the presence of a magnetic field along the quantization axis. For the angular dependence of the $C_3$ coefficient, we recover the dipole pattern $1-3\\cos (\\theta)^2$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate C3 coefficients for different angles\n",
    "c3_obj = pi.C3(ket1, ket2)\n",
    "c3_obj.set_diamagnetism_enabled(False)\n",
    "c3_obj.set_magnetic_field([0, 0, 20], \"gauss\")\n",
    "\n",
    "thetas = np.linspace(0, 2 * np.pi, 40)\n",
    "c3_coeffs = [c3_obj.set_angle(theta, unit=\"radian\").get(\"GHz um^3\") for theta in thetas]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the results\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].remove()\n",
    "axs[1] = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection=\"polar\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axs:\n",
    "    ax.scatter(thetas, c3_coeffs, label=\"perturbative C3\")\n",
    "    ax.plot(\n",
    "        thetas,\n",
    "        -0.5 * c3_coeffs[0] * (1 - 3 * np.cos(thetas) ** 2),\n",
    "        label=r\"$1-3\\cos(\\theta)^2$\",\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[0].legend()\n",
    "axs[0].set_xlabel(r\"$\\theta$ [rad]\")\n",
    "axs[0].set_ylabel(r\"$C_3$ [$h$ GHz $\\mu m^3$]\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x500 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate C6 coefficients for different angles\n",
    "c6_obj = pi.C6(ket1, ket1)\n",
    "c6_obj.set_diamagnetism_enabled(False)\n",
    "c6_obj.set_magnetic_field([0, 0, 20], \"gauss\")\n",
    "\n",
    "c6_coeffs = [c6_obj.set_angle(theta, unit=\"radian\").get(\"GHz um^6\") for theta in thetas]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot the results\n",
    "fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(10, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[1].remove()\n",
    "axs[1] = fig.add_subplot(1, 2, 2, projection=\"polar\")\n",
    "\n",
    "for ax in axs:\n",
    "    ax.scatter(thetas, c6_coeffs, label=\"perturbative C6\")\n",
    "\n",
    "axs[0].legend()\n",
    "axs[0].set_xlabel(r\"$\\theta$ [rad]\")\n",
    "axs[0].set_ylabel(r\"$C_6$ [$h$ GHz $\\mu m^6$]\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  }
 ],
